
[1]oratorio

   ORATO'RIO, n.

   1. In Italian music, a sacred drama of dialogues, containing
   recitatives, duets, trios, ritornellos, choruses, &c. The subjects are
   mostly taken from the Scriptures.

   2. A place of worship; a chapel.
